simgui (0.5.17-1) unstable; urgency=critical

  * CRITICAL FIX: Remove --noprompt from pySim-shell invocation.
    --noprompt prevented pySim-shell from reading piped stdin commands,
    causing verify_adm and all write operations to be silently ignored.
    This was the root cause of programming appearing to succeed while
    read-back verification correctly reported failure.
  * authenticate() via safe shell now correctly processes verify_adm.
  * _program_nonempty_card safe shell + piped commands now work.
  * Init-failure detection relies on output scanning (unchanged).
  * Updated tests: assert --noprompt is NOT present.

